    <centralBlocks>
      <Value><![CDATA[[
  {
    "key": "ae77a7d0-27bd-49b4-9618-1d412d8712d2",
    "name": "Why QMU",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Why QMU",
    "content": "<ul>\n<li>Placements give you the optimum balance of practical and theoretical learning.</li>\n<li>Smaller class sizes mean you will get close support and guidance from staff who get to know you.</li>\n<li>Graduate with a range of transferable business skills which are highly sought after by employers.</li>\n<li>Tailor your degree in Years Three and Four and study business management with another subject – enterprise, finance or marketing – and make your skills stand out.</li>\n</ul>"
  },
  {
    "key": "fa97c289-0faf-4d5c-9bc3-6377f3e59443",
    "name": "About the course",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "About the course",
    "content": "<p>People do business with people. If you have first-class management skills and practical expertise, people are going to want to be in business with you. The best companies will want you. That is why our business management options are designed to give you the knowledge and skills that you need to thrive as a business leader and manager in the fast-moving marketplaces of tomorrow.</p>\n<p>All students enrol on the general business management degree for Years One and Two. This is when you will build a strong foundation in core business management areas, marketing, economics, finance, human resource management, entrepreneurship, digital business and law.</p>\n<p>In Year Three you’ll choose which of the four named routes you wish to specialise towards. You can study for a general business management degree or focus on one particular area such as enterprise, finance or marketing. This will allow you to graduate with a specialist award, for example in BA (Hons) Business Management with Enterprise.</p>\n<p>Whichever business management path you take, you will be equipped with the skills employers are looking for, negotiation, project management, problem solving, critical thinking and team working.</p>\n<p>Your practical business expertise will be honed by placements, guest speakers from the business world, business projects and the creation of your own business plan. You will also have the opportunity (subject to availability) in Years Two or Three to study for one semester at a university overseas in North America, Canada, Hong Kong, Europe, New Zealand or Australia.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "20fb277c-bf5f-462f-90b4-d1ef94c67f19",
    "name": "Structure",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Structure",
    "content": "<p>You can study for an honours degree over four years or an ordinary degree over three years. You will complete a range of modules each year as outlined.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "2ad73590-eaa1-4193-9faa-dbbef05dbd8e",
    "name": "Modules",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Modules",
    "content": "<p>Year One is designed as an introductory year, which will not only introduce you to key subject matter in business, but will allow you to develop the skills and learning techniques required in university level education.</p>\n<p><strong>Year One</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Introduction to Marketing</li>\n<li>Introduction to Economics</li>\n<li>Introduction to Business in Society</li>\n<li>Introduction to Finance and Accounting</li>\n<li>Introduction to Management</li>\n<li>Entrepreneurship</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Year Two</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Operations Management</li>\n<li>Business Law</li>\n<li>Live Business Event</li>\n<li>Human Resource Management</li>\n<li>Digital Business and E-Commerce Management</li>\n<li>Negotiation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Year Three </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>New Enterprise Creation</li>\n<li>Research Methods and Skills</li>\n<li>Organisational Behaviour</li>\n<li>Project Management</li>\n<li>Two elective modules</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Year Four </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Strategy as Practice</li>\n<li>Placement</li>\n<li>Critical Issues in International Management</li>\n<li>One Elective Module</li>\n<li>Dissertation or Business Project</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The modules listed here are correct at time of posting (April 2021) but may differ slightly to those offered in 2022. Please check back here for any updates.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "3601a89c-127d-4986-825e-4635e576d3f5",
    "name": "Teaching, learning and assessment",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Teaching, learning and assessment",
    "content": "<p>You will be taught in lectures, seminars and practical workshops. Outside these formally timetabled sessions you will be expected to continue learning through self-study. You will be assessed by a range of methods such as written exams, reports, poster presentations, business plans, live pitch, group presentations and negotiation role play.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "d5891377-bee7-400e-9c76-091532f66bf5",
    "name": "Placements",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Placements",
    "content": "<p>You will complete a four-week placement in Year Four. Students are responsible for sourcing a placement host organisation, which can be in the UK or abroad. To help with the process, we hold a speed interview event on campus to match students with hosts offering placements.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "c4fd4d41-4860-4aa3-8e56-0f2ea5c2ffcc",
    "name": "Exchange opportunities",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Exchange opportunities",
    "content": "<p dir=\"LTR\" align=\"LEFT\">In Years Two or Three you have the opportunity (subject to availability) to study for one semester at a university overseas, in Europe, North America or Australia. <a data-udi=\"umb://document/1a73f579f0f34d2a9f4ddb6fa7b5ce94\" href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/61c8e09441eb44ae940a55266617ab37}\" title=\"Exchanges and Study Abroad\">More information on studying abroad</a>.  </p>\n<p>On December 24th 2020, the UK Government announced that as an outcome of Brexit negotiations, the United Kingdom would not be seeking to participate in the Erasmus+ successor programme.</p>\n<p>From 2022/23 Queen Margaret University will no longer operate under the Erasmus+ scheme. Over the coming year we will be working with new and existing partners on study abroad and exchange opportunities for the 2022/23 academic year and beyond.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "69abb1f3-ab54-487f-889f-9c2dc59f52eb",
    "name": "Careers",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Careers",
    "content": "<p>This is a degree that works. In general management, marketing, sales management, logistics, financial services, operations management and human resources management, our graduates are proving their worth to companies in the UK and internationally. Graduates have also set up their own businesses or taken their learning even further as postgraduate students. </p>\n<p><a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"https://www.bbc.co.uk/bitesize/articles/z4vpd6f\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lauren Leisk case study (BBC website)\">Case study of QMU Business Management graduate entrepreneur Lauren Leisk on BBC Bitesize</a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "6ecb659d-cd18-4d64-8098-59b270a5ddad",
    "name": "Entry requirements",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Entry requirements",
    "content": "<p>Scottish Higher: Standard - BBBC, Minimum - BCCC</p>\n<p>A Level: BCC</p>\n<p>Irish Leaving Certificate: H2 H3 H3 H3</p>\n<p>International Baccalaureate: 28 points</p>\n<p>International: IELTS of 6.0 with no element lower than 5.5</p>\n<p>Required subjects: English Required and Maths preferred at Nat 5/GCSE</p>\n<p>Mature/Access: We welcome applications from mature students with other relevant qualifications and/or experience. </p>\n<p>For more information on related HNC and HND courses, visit our <a href=\"/study-here/access-to-higher-education/college-leavers-and-mature-students/\" title=\"College Leavers and Mature Students Advice\">College Leavers and Mature Students Advice page</a>.</p>\n<p>Direct Entry:</p>\n<p><em>Year Two</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>HNC in a related subject with B in the graded unit</li>\n<li>Scottish Higher: BC at Advanced Higher in relevant subjects plus BB at Higher</li>\n<li>A Level: BBB in relevant subjects</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Year Three</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>HND in a related subject with CB in the graded unit</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For details of related HNC and HND courses, visit our <a href=\"/study-here/access-to-higher-education/college-leavers-and-mature-students/\" title=\"College Leavers and Mature Students Advice\">College Leavers and Mature Students Advice page</a>.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "9346547c-1728-4173-869a-e7870fb318c8",
    "name": "Industry links",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Industry links",
    "content": "<p>We are a member of the Chartered Association of Business Schools (CABS).</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "0b789624-b82f-462a-967a-3ec1f1f36066",
    "name": "Teaching staff, class sizes and timetables",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Teaching staff, class sizes and timetables",
    "content": "<p>For more information, please visit ‘<a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/363407ed108f454784361ca7c9d57713}\" title=\"How we teach and how you'll learn - Undergraduate\">How we teach and how you’ll learn’</a>.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "521fe3a4-c8c2-4eb7-a1c9-5b7534bfc8ea",
    "name": "Awarding body",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Awarding body",
    "content": "<p>More information is in the ‘External Review’ section of our ‘<a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/363407ed108f454784361ca7c9d57713}\" title=\"How we teach and how you'll learn - Undergraduate\" data-udi=\"umb://document/808ed3f70b49412b9304eaa6cb45dd5a\">How we teach and how you’ll learn</a>’ page.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "f3b0d6af-2687-4389-a5d0-e3290b853f56",
    "name": "View open day course presentation",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Open day course presentation",
    "content": "<div class=\"umb-loader\" style=\"height: 10px; margin: 10px 0px;\"></div>\n<div class=\"mceNonEditable embeditem\" data-embed-url=\"https://youtu.be/qpWvecvET7k\" data-embed-height=\"346\" data-embed-width=\"721\" data-embed-constrain=\"true\"><iframe width=\"524\" height=\"295\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/qpWvecvET7k?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"\" title=\"Business Management\"></iframe></div>"
  }
]]]></Value>
